HEADWORD: Lacinia
<hw>La*cin"i*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> L.
<plw>Lacini⟦ae⟧</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., the lappet or flap
of a garment.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>One
of the narrow, jagged, irregular pieces or divisions which form a sort
of fringe on the borders of the petals of some flowers.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>A narrow, slender portion of the edge of a
monophyllous calyx, or of any irregularly incised leaf.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The posterior, inner process of
the stipes on the maxill⟦ae⟧ of insects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Laciniated</ent>⟦br⟧
